King William's Town Two sisters hitch-hiking on the N2 near Colosa village in Dutywa died when they were hit by a car, Eastern Cape police said on Saturday. The car was travelling from Mthatha towards Dutywa when it struck the sisters late on Friday afternoon, Captain Jackson Manatha said. &quot;The cause of the accident is still under investigation by Dutywa police. The deceased were hitch hiking from Colosa village to Mpozolo village, Dutywa.&quot; A case of culpable homicide had been opened, he said. African News Agency